== History == [[File:FujisanSimomiyaOmuroSengenShrine Kayu-ura Ritual.jpg|thumb|The Kayu-ura Ritual performed annually at {{ill|Fujisan Shimomiya Omuro Sengen Shrine|ja|冨士山下宮小室浅間神社|12=draft}} by the Yoshinoike Onsen family]] Yoshinoike Onsen was founded in {{ill|1856|ja|1856年|12=draft}} ({{ill|Ansei era|ja|安政|12=draft}} 3). It operated as a ryokan until the prewar era and underwent renovations in 1989 (Heisei 1).
== Access == * '''Train''': 1-minute walk from {{ill|Yoshiike Onsen-mae Station|ja|葭池温泉前駅|12=draft}} on the {{ill|Fujikyuko Line|ja|富士山麓電気鉄道富士急行線|12=draft}}. * '''Car''': ** About 12 minutes from {{ill|Kawaguchiko Interchange|ja|河口湖インターチェンジ|12=draft}} or about 5 minutes from {{ill|Fujiyoshida Nishikatsura Smart Interchange|ja|富士吉田西桂スマートインターチェンジ|12=draft}} on the {{ill|Chuo Expressway|ja|中央自動車道|12=draft}}. ** About 12 minutes from {{ill|Fujiyoshida Interchange|ja|富士吉田インターチェンジ|12=draft}} on the {{ill|Higashi-Fujigoko Road|ja|東富士五湖道路|12=draft}}.
